@node background
vmem.library/--background---                     vmem.library/--background---


                       THE ** VIRTUAL MEMORY ** LIBRARY

                               ( VERSION 1 )

                       COPYRIGHT (c) 1994 BY LEE BRAIDEN


       These are the autodocs for programming vmem.library. VMem is a very
   simple set of six (6) functions, and four (4) macros. All you need to do
   to use VMem is :

       * Call @{"vmAllocBlock" link vmAllocBlock} (or use the macro @{"vmAllocData" link vmAllocData}) to get a control
         handle. (This is used by VMem to keep track of what's happening
         to your data).

       * Call @{"vmLock" link vmLock} (or use the macro @{"vmLockData" link vmLockData}) to get a lock on the
         data you wanna use at that time.

       * Access your data.

       * Call @{"vmUnLock" link vmUnLock} (or use the macro @{"vmUnLockData" link vmUnLockData}) to unlock the data
         again.

       * Call @{"vmFreeBlock" link vmFreeBlock} (or use the macro @{"vmFreeData" link vmFreeData}) to free the control
         handle you got by calling @{"vmAllocBlock" link vmAllocBlock} (or using @{"vmAllocData" link vmAllocData})


       The macro versions of the four functions just a simple way to alloc
   one element of data without the extra args required by the functions.
   (The functions have extra options to cope with array use.


       The other two (2) functions are replacements for exec.library's
   AllocMem() and FreeMem() functions. They provide a few more functions
   than exec's versions, including flushing Virtual Memory if exec's
   AllocMem would normally fail.

       See the individual autodocs below for a more detailed explanation.
@endnode
@node vmAllocBlock
vmem.library/vmAllocBlock                           vmem.library/vmAllocBlock

   NAME   
           vmAllocBlock

   SYNOPSIS
           vmBlock *vmb = vmAllocBlock(ULONG size,ULONG nels,ULONG memflags)
                     d0                  d0          d1          d2

   FUNCTION
           Allocates a vmBlock for control of data which will use virtual
       memory.

   INPUTS

       size:
       -   size of each element in array
       nels:
       -   number of elements in array
       memflags:
       -   standard exec.library/AllocMem() memory attribute flags

   RESULT

       vmb:
       -   Virtual memory control handle (vmBlock).This block stores
           information about your data,and is passed to the other
           virtual memory functions to let them know what state your
           data is in.

   EXAMPLE

       vmBlock *vmb;
       struct Preferences *prefs_ptr;/*largest structure I could think of*/
       ULONG i;
       ...

       if(!(vmb = @{"vmAllocBlock" link vmAllocBlock}(sizeof(struct Preferences),10,MEMF_PUBLIC)))
       {
           /*  vmAllocBlock failed - you're either *VERY* low on memory,
               or the the path that vmem.library is using is full */

           ...

       }else
       {
           for(i=0;i<NUM_ELS;i++)
           {
               if(!(prefs_ptr = @{"vmLock" link vmLock}(vmb,i)))
               {
                   /* data lock failed - disk error , or VERY low on mem */
                   ....

               }else
               {
                   /* you've got your data,do whatever you want with it */

                   ....

                   /*  unlock the data when you've finished with it,so vmem
                       will know when it's not in use */ 

                   @{"vmUnLock" link vmUnLock}(vmb,i);

               };
           };

           /*  when you've finished with all the data, free the control
               block */
                
          @{"vmFreeBlock" link vmFreeBlock}(vmb);
       };




   NOTES

   BUGS

       Doesn't handle saving across multiple disks/devices yet.

   SEE ALSO

       @{"vmFreeBlock" link vmFreeBlock},@{"vmLock" link vmLock},@{"vmUnLock" link vmUnLock},         @{"vmAllocData" link vmAllocData}
       exec.library/AllocMem autodoc (for memory flag definitions)
@endnode
@node vmAllocData
vmem.library/vmAllocData                             vmem.library/vmAllocData

   NAME

           vmAllocData         (MACRO)

   SYNOPSIS

           vmBlock *b = vmAllocData(ULONG blocksize,ULONG memflags);

   FUNCTION

       This is defined in Libraries/VMem.h as
       
            @{"vmAllocBlock" link vmAllocBlock}(blocksize,1,memflags)

       It just Allocates a vmBlock which isn't an array,i.e. Only contains
       one element.See that function's autodoc for details.
           
